baby ignore karo ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
baby ignore karo  Example 07 — Loops
baby ignore karo  jabtak, intezaar — both mean "while" / "keep waiting"
baby ignore karo  tab tak closes the loop header in natural style
baby ignore karo ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

~~ intezaar (natural style) — "wait until"
yaad i hai 1
intezaar i chhota ya barabar hai 5 tab tak
  bolo i
  i hai i milan 1
bas itna hi

~~ jabtak (core style) — same semantics
yaad j hai 10
jabtak j bada hai 0 tab tak
  baby bolo na j
  j hai j doori 3
bas itna hi

~~ Count words in a sentence using a loop
baby ignore karo  (simulating char count via manual digit loop)
yaad count hai 0
yaad limit hai 7
intezaar count chhota hai limit tab tak
  count hai count milan 1
bas itna hi
bolo "counted:"
bolo count

~~ Loop building a sum — word operators only
yaad total hai 0
yaad n hai 1
intezaar n chhota ya barabar hai 10 tab tak
  total hai total milan n
  n hai n milan 1
bas itna hi
bolo "sum 1 to 10:"
bolo total

~~ Nested loops — multiplication table corner
yaad row hai 1
intezaar row chhota ya barabar hai 3 tab tak
  yaad col hai 1
  intezaar col chhota ya barabar hai 3 tab tak
    bolo row milan " x " milan col milan " = " milan to_text(row intense col)
    col hai col milan 1
  bas itna hi
  row hai row milan 1
bas itna hi

love you baby byeee
